'''Herman Musaph''' ({{lang-nl|Heijman Musaph}}) (7 January 1915 – 18 November 1992) was a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[Holocaust survivor]], [[psychiatrist]], dermatologist and [[sexologist]].<ref>[http://www.inthe90s.com/generated/obit1992.shtml Inthe90s.com: Obit]</ref>
Musaph was born in [[Amsterdam]]. He studied medicine at the [[University of Amsterdam]]. In 1977 Musaph became Professor of Medicine at the [[University of Utrecht]]. He wrote various works on [[dermatology]].
Musaph founded the [[Dutch Society for Sexual Reform]] and he wrote the "Handbook of Sexology". He was the winner of the [[Magnus Hirschfeld Medal]] in 1990. The [[Herman Musaph Foundation for Psychodermatology]] is named in his honor.
Herman was married to [[Rosetta Andriesse]] and had no children.
